<subSubSection id="7B18050A8EB468B4D1255348F34E20DF" pageId="419" pageNumber="420" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5342BCC233004FCA54C3F8D0F6A4EE55" pageId="419" pageNumber="420">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="041D30D2801DA2D9736262D1768CDE06" pageId="419" pageNumber="420">
The range of this species extends from the Aleutian Islands and the Gulf of Alaska coast to southwestern Yukon Territory (Lindroth 1963b: 273, as 
<taxonomicName id="9EE669E0BFD6B9A065D6037EF01E3EDC" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="419" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incertum">
<emphasis id="E5206ED3DF135E886A1A954C30F2E050" italics="true" pageId="419" pageNumber="420">Bembidion incertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), south to north-central New Mexico (Fall and Cockerell 1907: 157; Hayward 1897: 68, as 
<taxonomicName id="43263E9B782B27ED492430D905A0EE6E" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="419" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incertum">
<emphasis id="FE6DD87B7496406887B9C624FDE07019" italics="true" pageId="419" pageNumber="420">Bembidion incertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) along the Rocky Mountains and to the Sierra Nevada in eastern California (Casey 1918: 30, as 
<taxonomicName id="5803CAF1856B6CCDFD82ABA850621E1C" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="419" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testatum">
<emphasis id="8D869C9109AD48204E28C1F8AD6B55A0" italics="true" pageId="419" pageNumber="420">Bembidion testatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
